{{infobox country at games | NPC = CRC | NPCname = Comite Paralimpico de Costa Rica | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Costa Rica|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Costa Rica]]''' made its '''[[Paralympic Games]]''' début at the [[1992 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Barcelona]], sending just two representatives to compete in men's [[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Paralympics|track and field]]. Absent in 1996, it returned in 2000, and has participated in every edition of the [[Summer Paralympics]] since then. Its delegations have always been small: a single athlete in track and field in 2000; a single swimmer in 2004; two table tennis players in 2008.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=CRC&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Costa Rica at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
Costa Rica has never taken part in the Winter Paralympics, and no Costa Rican has ever won a Paralympic medal.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=CRC&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Costa Rica at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
==See also== * [[Costa Rica at the Olympics]]
