{{use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = DEN | NOCname = [[National Olympic Committee and Sports Confederation of Denmark]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1960 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.dif.dk }}&nbsp;{{da icon}} {{en icon}} | location = [[Rome]] | competitors = 100 (88 men and 12 women) | sports = 15 | flagbearer = [[Benny Schmidt]] | rank = 13 | gold = 2 | silver = 3 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = [[Denmark at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games }}
'''[[Denmark]]''' competed at the '''[[1960 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]. 100 competitors, 88 men and 12 women, took part in 46 events in 15 sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/DEN/summer/1960/ |title=Denmark at the 1960 Rome Summer Games |accessdate=3 August 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref> Cyclist [[Knud Enemark Jensen]] died during the [[Cycling at the 1960 Summer Olympics – Men's team time trial|team time trial]].<ref name="Jensen">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/je/knud-enemark-jensen-1.html |title=Knud Enemark Jensen |accessdate=3 August 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>
==Medalists== ===Gold=== * [[Paul Elvstrøm]] — Sailing, men's Finn individual competition * [[Erik Hansen (canoeist)|Erik Hansen]] — Canoeing, men's K1 1,000 metres kayak singles
===Silver=== * [[Hans Fogh]] and [[Ole Erik Petersen]] — Sailing, Flying Dutchman * [[William Berntsen]], [[Steen Christensen (sailor)|Steen Christensen]] and [[Søren Hancke]] — Sailing, 5.5 Metre * [[Paul Andersen]], [[John Danielsen]], [[Henning Enoksen]], [[Henry From]], [[Bent Hansen]], [[Poul Jensen (footballer born 1934)|Poul Jensen]], [[Flemming Nielsen]], [[Hans Nielsen (footballer)|Hans Nielsen]], [[Harald Nielsen]], [[Poul Pedersen]], [[Jørn Sørensen]] and [[Tommy Troelsen]] — Football (soccer), men's team competition
===Bronze=== * [[Erik Hansen (canoeist)|Erik Hansen]], [[Arne Høyer]], [[Erling Jessen]] and [[Helmut Sørensen]] — Canoeing, men's K1 4x500 metres kayak relay
