The [[The Football Association|FA's]] Charter Standard Award recognises and rewards high quality of levels of provision in club, [[The Football League|league]] and schools football. There three levels of [[The Football Association|FA]] Charter Standard Award for organisations to recognise the different standards. The entry level is an 'FA Charter Standard Club', the next is an 'FA Charter Development Club', and the most advanced is the 'FA Charter Community Club'.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/GetIntoFootball/parentsandvolunteers/Runningaclub/Runningaclub/CharterStandard|title=get into football|accessdate=13 December 2012|work=thefa.com}}</ref>
Since it was launched in 2001, the award has been granted to 4,500 clubs with 460 advanced level [[Community club]]s and 120 leagues, and there are now over 2,500 Charter Standard Award Schools in [[England]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.semley.wilts.sch.uk/manage_contents_files/FA%20Charter%20Mark%20Newsletter.pdf |title=charter standard schools newsletter |accessdate=13 November 2012 |work=semley.wilts.sch.uk |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120916124012/http://www.semley.wilts.sch.uk/manage_contents_files/FA%20Charter%20Mark%20Newsletter.pdf |archivedate=16 September 2012 |df= }}</ref>
