{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Mount Pleasant | nickname = | country = England | location = [[Batley]], [[West Yorkshire]] | establishment = 1869 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1883 | club1 = T Emmett's XI | date = 23 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/304.html Ground profile | image = Batley Cricket Club - Purlwell Hall Road (geograph 3403909).jpg }}
'''Mount Pleasant''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Batley]], [[West Yorkshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1869, when Batley played Burnley.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/304_misc.html Other matches played on Mount Pleasant]</ref> The ground hosted a single [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1883 when the T. Emmett's XI played R. G. Barlow's XI.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/304_f.html First-Class Matches played on Mount Pleasant]</ref>
The ground, adjacent to the [[Mount Pleasant, Batley|stadium]] of [[Batley Bulldogs|Batley RLFC]], is the home of Batley Cricket Club. They are members of the [[Bradford Premier League|Central Yorkshire Cricket League]].
